<p>
<b>Environment, Energy, and Science: Agriculture
</b>
</center>
<p>
<ul>
<b>Books:</b>
<p>
<a href="/heritage/congress/chapt3.html">How the 104th Congress Cut  Red Tape and Returned Common Sense to Regulation</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/antonel.htm">Angela Antonelli</a>. (<i>Reviewing the Revolution: Conservative Successes in the 104th Congress</i>)
<br>
<a href="/heritage/issues96/chpt4.html">The Environment</a> by John Shanahan.  (<i>Issues '96: The Candidate's Briefing Book</i>)<p>
<b>Policy Papers:</b>
<p>
<li>4/30/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/enviro/fyi98.html">What the New Farm Bill Will Mean to State Economies and Farmers</a> by John Frydenlund and <a href="/heritage/staff/winston.htm">David H. Winston</a>. (F.Y.I. #98)  
<li>2/28/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/enviro/ib221.html">Agriculture Reform: Can House Succeed Where Senate Failed?</a> by John Frydenlund. (Issue Bulletin #221)
<li>2/26/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/enviro/em448.html">How the Proposed Dairy "Reform" Will Impose Heavy Costs on Americans</a> by John Frydenlund. (Executive Memorandum #448)
<li>11/9/95 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/enviro/ib219.html">How To Salvage Agriculture Reforms in Budget Reconciliation</a> by John Frydenlund. (Issue Bulletin #219)
<li>9/26/95 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/enviro/ib216.html">Reform the Sugar, Peanut, and Dairy Programs</a> by John Frydenlund (Issue Bulletin #216)
<li>9/19/95 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/enviro/ib214.html">How Freeing America's Farmers Would Mean A $135 Billion Boost</a> by John E. Frydenlund and <a href="/heritage/staff/winston.htm">David H. Winston</a>. (Issues Bulletin #214)



<li>6/16/95 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/enviro/em417.html">Why Budget Debate Must Not Sideline Agriculture Reform</a> by John Frydenlund. (Executive Memorandum #417)
