<HEAD>

<TITLE>Cyberspace and the American Dream -- PFF</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Rick F. O'Donnell">
<META NAME="OPERATOR" CONTENT="Michael Sparks">
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="backgrnd.gif" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"  LINK="#8C1717" VLINK="#545454" ALINK="#FF0000">
<map name="cft">
<area shape="rect" coords="0,0,92,20" href="#cyber">
<area shape="rect" coords="93,0,193,20" href="#fcc">
<area shape="rect" coords="194,0,318,20" href="#telco"></map>

<blockquote>

<a href="welcome.html"><img src="bi.gif" align="right" border="0" alt="PFF"></a>
<center>
<a href="wst.map"><img src="cft.gif" border="0" USEMAP="#cft" ISMAP></a>
<img src="cadhead.gif" alt="Cyberspace and the American Dream">
</center>
<br><br><P>
Much of our recent work on telecom has been enhanced by the  
<a href = "http://www.pff.org/pff/workin~1.htm"><big>FCC Working Group.</big></a>

<p>

<table>
<tr>
<td valign="top" width="20%">PFF is working to describe what a Transformation of American Life
driven by the new technologies of the information revolution really
means.  How will it change our fundamental values and beliefs?
 Society's elemental relationships?   The organization and workings
of our economy?  And our political compact with ourselves [or
is it, after all, between us and the state]?
<P>
If we can describe what is to come, we can show what is to be
done.  In addition, policy change is taking place in Washington,
in state legislatures, indeed, in governments around the world,
as policymakers attempt to understand the consequences of the
move from an analog to a digital world and its impact on regulatory
policy.  PFF is actively involved in the telecommunications debate,
focusing on the next generation of deregulation.
<td valign="top">
<a name="cyber"></a>
<img src="bullet.gif" hspace="5" align="top"><big>The Nature of Cyberspace</big>
<UL>



<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" vspace="4" align="top">
<b><a href="/pff/21fcc1.html">The FCC and the Telecommunications Act of 1996: Putting Competition on Hold?</a></b>
by G.A. Keyworth, II and Jeffrey A. Eisenach<br>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" vspace="4" align="top">
<b><a href="/pff/encry.html">The Computer Revolution, Encryption And
True Threats To National Security</a></b>
by G.A. Keyworth, II and
David E. Colton, Esq.<br>  
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" vsapce="4" align="top"><b><a href="/pff/cad/pr0620.html">Administration Undermines Information Age National Security</a></b><br>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" vspace="4" align="top"><b><a href="/pff/cad/5-2a.html">Freedom to Pray and Sin</a></b> by Richard O'Donnell<br>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" vspace="4" align="top"><b><a href="/pff/cad/5-2.html">Courting Irrelevance</a></b> by  
Richard O'Donnell<br>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" vspace="4" align="top"><b><a href="http://www.house.gov/white/internet_caucus/netcauc.html">The Congressional Internet Caucus</b></a> provides a forum to communicate with your elected officials.<br>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" vspace="4" align="top"><b><a href="aspen-mv.html">Message from Aspen</b></a> by Michael Vlahos<br>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" vspace="4" align="top"><a href="tsot-1.html"><b>People and Society in Cyberspace</a></b> by Jay Keyworth<br>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" vspace="4" align="top"><a href="Analog.html"><b>Analog to Digital, That is the Issue</a></b> by Jay Keyworth<br>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" vspace="4" align="top"><a href="pff6.html"><b>From Virtuality to Reality</a></b> by Newt Gingrich<br>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" vspace="4" align="top"><a href="position.html"><b>A Magna Carta for the Knowledge Age</a></b> by Esther Dyson, George Gilder, Jay Keyworth and Alvin Toffler
<P>
</ul>
<a name="fcc"></a>
<img src="bullet.gif" align="top" hspace=5"><big>Replacing the FCC</Big>
<UL>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" vspace="4" align="top">The Telecommunications Act of 1996>: <a href="/pff/cad/patr051496.html">Intent, Impact and Implications</a>.  By Dennis R. Patrick<br>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" vs[ace="4" align="top"><a href="http://khht.com/huber/h
ome.html"<b>Testimony by Peter Huber,</b></a> FCC Working Group Member, before the 
Subcommittee on Government Management<br>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" vs[ace="4" align="top"><a href="/pff/cad/ct0401b.html"><b>Testimony of Peter Pitsch</b></a> on the FCC<br>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" vspace="4" align="top"><a href="/pff/cad/pits0305.html"><b>Testimony of Peter Pitsch before the FCC</a></b> on Spectrum Allocation<br>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" vspace="4" align="top"><b><a href="/pff/cpr/fcc0304.html">On The Road to Digital Freedom</a></b> Our plan to further dismantle the FCC.<br>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" vspace="4" align="top"><b><a href="abolish_fcc.html">Plan to Abolish FCC Unveiled</b></a><br>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" vspace="4" align="top"><a href="telecom_revolution.html"><b>FCC Replacement Plan</a></b>:  The Telecom Revolution - An American Opportunity<br>
</UL>
<a name="telco"></a>
<img src="bullet.gif" align="top" hspace="5"><Big>Telecommunications Deregulation Policy</Big>
<UL>
<img src="/pff/diamond.gif" hspace="5" vspace="4" align="top">
