     New Appeal."  <i>Business Week</i> (July 19), pp. 130-131.
<blockquote>
          Believes that discussion of flat-rate tax has been
          helpful in drawing attention to the relationship
          between tax rates and the tax base.
</blockquote><p>
Will, George F. 1992.  "Brown's Burlesque."  <i>Washington Post</i> (April 9).
<blockquote>
                    A prominent conservative columnist supports Brown
          proposal and attacks progressivity.
</blockquote><p>
Yin, George K. 1995.  "Accomodating the 'Low-Income' in a Cash-Flow or Consumed Income Tax World."  <i>Florida Tax Review</i>,
     vol. 2, no. 8, pp. 445-491.
<blockquote>
          Finds that the EITC is not feasible under a
          consumption-based tax system.  Therefore, such a tax
          system cannot be as beneficial to the poor as the
          current tax system.
</blockquote><p>
Yoder, Edwin M., Jr. 1982.  "The Fever Over the Flat Tax."  <i>Washington Post</i> (July 14).
<blockquote>
          Sees nothing wrong with tax loopholes and therefore
          little to be gained from flat-rate. 
</blockquote><p>
<p>
<a href="#quick">Back to QuickLinks</a><p>
